parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS valve regulator can cause the anti-lock braking system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of braking ability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is on
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle accelerates instead of stopping when applying the brakes
the vehicle skids or locks up when braking
poor brake performance
soft brake pedal
and limited braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission flips
the vehicle slows down
loss of drive forward or backward
failure to shift properly
transmission fluid leak
transmission failure without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including stalling, loss of power, and even electrical fires, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or cuts off while driving
especially at high speeds; the vehicle stalls intermittently; the inside lights overheat; the alternator malfunctions
causing a no-start condition or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start; the alternator malfunctions
causing a no-start condition or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring harness issues can cause electrical fires, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
